TY Julie, 

But as a moderator here I want to say to all of you, it is not having or
owning anything that makes you an asset to this group. Being a member with
codes of ethics, decency, morals, and great insight of whether not to share,
or share or learn what others are doing is important to you and you alone.
This is a public forum with standards we tried to adhere to. Different
people for different ways for research, exploration or just out of curiosity
are welcomed here. Owning FB Box is not a prerequisite to being an ASSET to
any group. Please, all feel comfortable here and relax and enjoy what
everyone here is doing. Everyone enjoys everyone&#39;s work whether someone
replies or not. Let&#39;s keep this a smooth flowing public forum filled with
trust and courtesy for all. Enjoy and happy researching and exploring!

Blessings to ALL Members

Laura



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
juli velazquez
Sent: Saturday, February 02, 2008 10:52 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Yeah--it works.



Your very welcome Laura, and just an FYI, I don&#39;t have a Frank&#39;s Box.  I
would never ask for one.  I appreciate your dedication to this field, and I
am sure once you get one your box, you will be an asset to the group!



Looking forward to hearing your files!  



Juli



Laura Kimberley &lt;gjk1rrfan@...&gt; wrote:

Thank you Julie, for the kindness in your words to remind me that you think
I am begging and should take it private email. I see you have a box so your
tolerance of course is not quite like the others. I only wanted one simply
to communicate with friends and family and myself spiritually and nothing
else. Like taking it on the road. That I have no desire what&#39;s so ever. I
wanted one for strictly personal use. But, I am a smart lady and will build
my own and share I get with Frank privately. 

Please, be more considerate on this board. I shall not ask again. J Thanks
so much again for your reply,

Laura

